<subSubSection pageNumber="886" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="886">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="886">Note:</emphasis>
A later homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Jacq. (1762)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1763" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Thlaspi" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpestre">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="886">T. alpestre</emphasis>
Jacq. (1762)
</taxonomicName>
and hence illegitimate. There has been some confusion in the way the Linnaean name has been either used or synonymised (see review by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kerguélen">Kerguelen</normalizedToken>
&amp; al. in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="886">Lejeunia</emphasis>
n.s., 120: 175. 1987), which was clarified by the typification made by Marhold &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mártonfi">Martonfi</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
